{
  "title": "ISic001097. M. Valerius Chorton honoured as euergetes",
  "body": "<div id=\"editions\"><div class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Andoni Llamazares; edition source: <a href=\"https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/Q2SBPG9F\">https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/Q2SBPG9F</a></div><div id=\"edition-interpretive\">  <span class=\"textpartnumber\" id=\"abA\">section A</span>  <div class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\"><span class=\"ab\" id=\"divA--interpretive\">  <a id=\"aA-l1-interpretive\"><!--0--></a><span class=\"linenumber\">1</span>οἱ δεκορίωνες <br id=\"aA-l2-interpretive\"><span class=\"linenumber\">2</span><span data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Μάρκον Οὐαλέριον Διογνήτου\n                    Μῆγα υἱὸν Χόρτωνα\"><span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"praenomen\" data-text=\"Μάρκον\">Μ(άρκον)</span>  <span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"nomen\" data-text=\"Οὐαλέριον\">Οὐαλέριον</span>  <span data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Διογνήτου\n                    Μῆγα\"><span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"patronymic\" data-text=\"Διογνήτου\">Διογνήτου</span>  <br id=\"aA-l3-interpretive\"><span class=\"linenumber\">3</span><span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"patronymic\" data-text=\"Μῆγα\">Μῆγα</span></span>  <span data-text=\"υἱὸν\">υἱὸν</span>  <span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"cognomen\" data-text=\"Χόρτωνα\">Χόρτωνα</span></span>  <br id=\"aA-l4-interpretive\"><span class=\"linenumber\">4</span>εὐεργέταν </span></div>  <span class=\"textpartnumber\" id=\"abB\">section B</span>  <div class=\"textpart\" lang=\"la\"><span class=\"ab\" id=\"divB--interpretive\">  <a id=\"aB-l1-interpretive\"><!--0--></a><span class=\"linenumber\">1</span>ordo et populus civit(atis) Lilybit(anorum) <br id=\"aB-l2-interpretive\"><span class=\"linenumber\">2</span>patrono perpetuo </span></div>  <p class=\"miniapp\"></p></div><div class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Andoni Llamazares; edition source: <a href=\"https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/Q2SBPG9F\">https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/Q2SBPG9F</a></div><div id=\"edition-diplomatic\"><span class=\"textpartnumber\" id=\"abA\">section A</span><div class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\"><span class=\"ab\" id=\"divA--diplomatic\"><a id=\"aA-l1-diplomatic\"><!--0--></a><span class=\"linenumber\">1</span>ΟΙΔΕΚΟΡΙΩΝΕΣ<br id=\"aA-l2-diplomatic\"><span class=\"linenumber\">2</span><span data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Μάρκον Οὐαλέριον Διογνήτου\n                    Μῆγα υἱὸν Χόρτωνα\"><span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"praenomen\" data-text=\"Μάρκον\">Μ</span><span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"nomen\" data-text=\"Οὐαλέριον\">ΟΥΑΛΕΡΙΟΝ</span><span data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Διογνήτου\n                    Μῆγα\"><span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"patronymic\" data-text=\"Διογνήτου\">ΔΙΟΓΝΗΤΟΥ</span><br id=\"aA-l3-diplomatic\"><span class=\"linenumber\">3</span><span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"patronymic\" data-text=\"Μῆγα\">ΜΗΓΑ</span></span><span data-text=\"υἱὸν\">ΥΙΟΝ</span><span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"cognomen\" data-text=\"Χόρτωνα\">ΧΟΡΤΩΝΑ</span></span><br id=\"aA-l4-diplomatic\"><span class=\"linenumber\">4</span>ΕΥΕΡΓΕΤΑΝ</span></div><span class=\"textpartnumber\" id=\"abB\">section B</span><div class=\"textpart\" lang=\"la\"><span class=\"ab\" id=\"divB--diplomatic\"><a id=\"aB-l1-diplomatic\"><!--0--></a><span class=\"linenumber\">1</span>ORDOETPOPULUSCIVITLILYBIT<br id=\"aB-l2-diplomatic\"><span class=\"linenumber\">2</span>PATRONOPERPETUO</span></div><p class=\"miniapp\"></p></div></div>  <div id=\"facsimile-images\"><h2>Facsimile Images</h2></div>  <div id=\"apparatus\"><h4>Apparatus criticus</h4><ul><li><span><span>text of IG following Torremuzza, after Tardia</span></span></li></ul></div>  <div id=\"translation\"><h2> translation</h2><p class=\"translation-author\">  </p><p>  </p></div>  <div id=\"commentary\"><h2>commentary</h2>  <p>The inscription is similar to a more garbled text transmitted by Gualtherus and Tardia and observed at Mazara del Vallo (<a href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic001096\" target=\"_blank\">ISic001096</a> = IG XIV.273). An honorific for the father, Diognetos Megas was found in Marsala in the 20th century and provides confirmation of the tradition (SEG 34.951 = <a href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic001660\" target=\"_blank\">ISic001660</a>. The text is unusual for the Greek transcription of the latin word decurio, seemingly in the sense of 'bouleutes'. The presence of the term, together with the associated Latin inscripition on the side (although whether this is contemporary or a later addition is impossible to know) strongly suggest a date after the 40s BCE; but the existence of the more traditionally late Hellenistic Greek inscripiton for the father in turn make a later date almost impossible. </p>  </div>  <div id=\"bibliography\"><h2>bibliography</h2>  <ul><li> 34.0951 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000796\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000796</a></li><li> Franz 1853 5495 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001250\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001250</a></li><li> Mommsen 1883 <a href=\"http://arachne.uni-koeln.de/books/CILv10pII1883\" target=\"_blank\">7240</a>  <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000589\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000589</a></li><li> Kaibel 1890 <a href=\"https://clio.columbia.edu/catalog/6873760\" target=\"_blank\">277 </a>  <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001072\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001072</a></li><li> Hoffmann 1904 5211 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000817\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000817</a></li><li> Cagnat 1906 499 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001116\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001116</a></li><li> Robert 1960 278 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001623\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001623</a></li><li> Mason 1974 10 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001383\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001383</a></li><li> cf. Di Stefano 1984 146-149 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002035\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002035</a>  </li><li> Manganaro 1988 19 n.71 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001427\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001427</a></li><li> Wilson 1990 317 n. 15, 361 n.107 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001509\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001509</a></li></ul>  <ul><li></li></ul>  </div>  <div id=\"handnote\"><p>The manuscript tradition records rhomboid closed omega; Torremuzza after Tardia also records lunate sigma.</p> Line 1     Interlineation line 1 to 2     </div><div id=\"license\"> Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence.  </div>",
